            "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
            "body": "The trouble is you can't actually do a whole lot with these - you can get whether its Windows/Mac/Linux, and the Python version, but that's basically the only thing that you can make decisions on with `DEF` and `IF`. You can't use them to access C defines for example.\r\n\r\nAnd they break the general rule that the .c file you generate should not depend on the system you run it on (because it's quite frequent to distribute Cython-generated .c files with pip).\r\n\r\nPretty much the only useful thing is to `DEF` a static array length, and that's rarely necessary.",
